### Complexity Analysis

* **Time Complexity:** $O(n \times n \times \text{max\_element})$
Because we instantly prune any cell that returns a dead-end by setting `mat[i][j] = 0`, each cell in the $n \times n$ matrix is evaluated fully exactly **once**. For each cell, we check up to `max_jump` options.
* **Auxiliary Space:** $O(1)$ if we ignore the output matrix and recursion stack space, as we are reusing the given `mat` matrix to store visited dead-ends. System stack space will take at most $O(n)$ depth.
